metadata.name: Piel Morena
metadata.description:
This photo features a native dancer of the city of Valladolid in Yucatán, México. 

She dons a traditional Mayan Huipil and is adorned with ribbons and floral arrangements. Taken at the Zocalo, the public square located in front of the city's church, traditional dancers gather to share their music and dance with tourists and locals.
